theorem closure_interior_closure_eq_closure_of_isOpen
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : IsOpen (A : Set X)) :
    closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) = closure A := by
  -- We prove the equality via two inclusions.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `⊆` direction: monotonicity of `closure`.
    exact closure_mono
      (interior_subset :
        interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure A)
  · -- `⊇` direction: `A ⊆ interior (closure A)` since `A` is open.
    have hSub : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
      interior_maximal (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A) hA
    -- Taking closures yields the desired inclusion.
    have hIncl : closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) :=
      closure_mono hSub
    simpa using hIncl

theorem interior_closure_interior_subset_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
  exact
    interior_mono
      (closure_mono (interior_subset (A := (A : Set X))))

theorem P1_implies_P1_of_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 (A : Set X) → Topology.P1 (interior A) := by
  intro hP1
  dsimp [Topology.P1] at hP1 ⊢
  intro x hxInt
  -- From `x ∈ interior A`, we know `x ∈ A`.
  have hxA : x ∈ (A : Set X) :=
    (interior_subset : interior A ⊆ A) hxInt
  -- Apply `P1` for `A` to place `x` in `closure (interior A)`.
  have hxCl : x ∈ closure (interior A) := hP1 hxA
  -- Since `interior (interior A) = interior A`, the goal follows directly.
  simpa [interior_interior] using hxCl
